args: I ate so much... I partied sooo muuuch...
It was all too good to pass up...\nI think I'm gonna burst...
We played hanetsuki, we flew kites,\nwe spun tops around...
Hinomoto's New Year's goes hard,\nand it's all so damn much fun!\nBut I want a rematch on those tops.
How many rounds does this make?!
It seems you've enjoyed a Hinomotoan\nNew Year to its fullest.
Absolutely! Thanks for teaching me so\nmuch about it, both of you.
Well then, sounds like it's time to draw\nthings to a close.
Aw, can't we keep it going\njust a LITTLE longer?
If every day were New Year's,\nit wouldn't feel so special.
It's wonderful precisely because you only\nget one short taste of it each year.
I get all that, but it's still hard\nto switch out of party mode.
Then why don't we do the first calligraphy\nof the year to help get us motivated?
At the start of the year, we write down\ngoals and ideals for the new year to help\nfocus our resolves.
And as we use a brush to write them out,\nit's also an act of dedication to improving\none's penmanship.
Hey, NOW you're talking! After writing all\nthose nengajo out, I've gotten pretty good\nwith the ol' brush!
Heh. You're gonna have to prove it!
Let's get our goals clear in our minds so\nthey might guide us in the year to come.
I got a lot of practice in with nengajo—\nthough this one's thicker than my old one.
Yep! It's 'cause of my friends that I got\nto have such an incredible New Year's.
Plus, you made me realize a few things.\nEven inspired me to go back and ring in\nthe new year in my hometown.
All in all, this New Year's has taught me\nthat the most important things in life\nare my good pals.
And whatever changes come,\nI know that'll be constant.
Anyway, I wrote this out in the hopes\nI never take it for granted.
Something unchanging throughout the\nyears is quite beautiful indeed.
Heh. Thanks. And thanks again to all\nof you for helping me remember that.
And why is it giving me deja vu...?
I was supposed to take that fiend\nI decorated back to the forest!
Must've finally busted out of its cage.\nWhoopsie!
I guess a fiend showing up finally\npushed him over his limit...

Let's hope his new year's resolution is
to learn a little more control. Anyhoo,
we better help out before those two
wreck the entire place.
Come, everyone! We've a fiend to capture!
Uh oh. Looks like I missed my cue.
It was all so lovely, but then...chaos.
I didn't even get the chance to hand out\nthese gift envelopes.
With money inside, yes? That's another\nHinomotoan New Year's tradition, I recall.
Yep. When I heard Luca was studying their\nculture so diligently, I thought he deserved\na little reward.
Perhaps it is for the best. You'll likely\nneed those funds to repair the castle.
Well, at least we know this new year\nwon't be a boring one!
